docs.abstract: Facebook, Google and other major tech firms were every student’s dream workplaces. Until they weren’t.
docs.snippet: Facebook, Google and other major tech firms were every student’s dream workplaces. Until they weren’t.
docs.lead_paragraph: In 2006, Google bought YouTube for more than $1 billion, Apple was preparing to announce the first iPhone, and the American housing bubble began to deflate. Claire Stapleton, then a senior at the University of Pennsylvania, faced the same question over and over: What did she plan to do with that English degree? She flirted, noncommittally, with Teach for America.

docs.abstract: The victory was a remarkable comeback for Ms. Tsai and suggested that Beijing’s pressure campaign had backfired.
docs.snippet: The victory was a remarkable comeback for Ms. Tsai and suggested that Beijing’s pressure campaign had backfired.
docs.lead_paragraph: TAIPEI, Taiwan — Taiwan’s voters delivered a stinging rebuke of China’s rising authoritarianism on Saturday by re-electing President Tsai Ing-wen, who vowed to preserve the island’s sovereignty in the face of Beijing’s intensifying efforts to bring it under its control.

headline.main: In Blow to Beijing, Taiwan Re-elects Tsai Ing-wen as President
headline.print_headline: Taiwan Voters Re-elect President in a Rebuke To Beijing’s Authority

byline.original: By Steven Lee Myers and Chris Horton

docs.abstract: Not that long ago, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were golden in the eyes of the news media and public. What happened?
docs.snippet: Not that long ago, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were golden in the eyes of the news media and public. What happened?
docs.lead_paragraph: LONDON — Once upon a short time ago, the Duke and Duchess of Sussex were lauded as the breath of fresh air that the British monarchy needed to become more inclusive and modern.

headline.main: Harry, Meghan and Britain: When Did the Fairy Tale Go Sour?
headline.print_headline: The Duke, the Duchess and Britain: When Did the Fairy Tale Go Sour?
